).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369BB733966B21B6CC99FB41BF62" blockId="4.[151,1437,1445,1974]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis id="B908EA89B733966B21B6CC99FE4DBE66" bold="true" box="[199,457,1517,1542]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">
<typeStatus id="54C78839B733966B21B6CC99FEB0BE66" box="[199,308,1517,1542]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Holotype</typeStatus>
description.
</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4C849B7EB733966B235ACC99FD01BE65" box="[555,645,1517,1542]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" unit="mm" value="4.6">4.6 mm</quantity>
. Vertex of head red, pronotum blue-green, elytra brown with 
<number id="3DB424BCB733966B2436CC99FAD1BE66" box="[1351,1365,1517,1542]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" value="6.0">6</number>
(
<number id="3DB424BCB733966B2416CC9AFAF0BE66" box="[1383,1396,1518,1542]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" value="3.0">3</number>
+ 
<number id="3DB424BCB733966B24F7CC9AFA17BE66" box="[1414,1427,1518,1542]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" value="3.0">3</number>
) spots of yellow pubescence. 
<emphasis id="B908EA89B733966B209CCF65FDA9BE4A" bold="true" box="[493,557,1553,1578]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Head</emphasis>
with frons red, glabrous, with sculpture characterized by large punctures. Clypeus flat, depressed, green, without transverse carina. Antennae serrate from fifth segment. 
<emphasis id="B908EA89B733966B25CBCF41FAB7BE2E" bold="true" box="[1210,1331,1589,1614]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Pronotum</emphasis>
wider on the posterior half. Disc with transverse striae. Premarginal carinula not entire, up to almost half the length of pronotum, surrounded by sparse white setae. Marginal carinae joined before the base. Mentonniere with anterior margin rounded. Prosternal plate wide, with rounded apex. 
<emphasis id="B908EA89B733966B2242CFD5FC2EBEDA" bold="true" box="[819,938,1697,1722]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Scutellum</emphasis>
transversely carinate. 
<emphasis id="B908EA89B733966B25D9CFD5FA98BEDA" bold="true" box="[1192,1308,1697,1722]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Abdomen</emphasis>
with white pubescence on lateroterga, metepisterna and metacoxae. 
<emphasis id="B908EA89B733966B2261CFB1FCCCBEBE" bold="true" box="[784,840,1733,1758]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Legs</emphasis>
metallic green. All claws simply toothed. Metatarsus shorter than metatibia. Basal metatarsomere shorter than the sum of the following two (
<number id="3DB424BCB733966B251ACF9EFBF1BF62" box="[1131,1141,1770,1794]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" value="1.0">1</number>
&lt;
<number id="3DB424BCB733966B25F6CF9EFB13BF62" box="[1159,1175,1770,1794]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DB424BCB733966B25D8CF9EFB33BF62" box="[1193,1207,1770,1794]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" value="3.0">3</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3666510B733966B21B6CE79FD75BF46" box="[199,753,1805,1830]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC3369BB733966B21B6CE79FD75BF46" blockId="4.[151,1437,1445,1974]" box="[199,753,1805,1830]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis id="B908EA89B733966B21B6CE79FECABF46" bold="true" box="[199,334,1805,1830]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name relates to the 
<typeStatus id="54C78839B733966B2311CE7AFD14BF46" box="[608,656,1806,1830]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3666510B733966A21B6CE45FBDAB9AF" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="580" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC3369BB733966A21B6CE45FC15B881" blockId="4.[151,1437,1445,1974]" lastBlockId="5.[159,1421,204,463]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="580" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis id="B908EA89B733966B21B6CE45FECBBF2A" bold="true" box="[199,335,1841,1866]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D18B733966B202BCE45FE75BF29" box="[346,497,1841,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quito">
<emphasis id="B908EA89B733966B202BCE45FE75BF29" box="[346,497,1841,1865]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Agrilus quito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to a group characterized by the pronotum being blue-green, by median pubescence of elytra Y-shaped or inverted “T”, and rounded elytral apex. In this group, in size and shape, the species most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D18B733966B20D5CE0EFE7ABFF1" box="[420,510,1914,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quito">
<emphasis id="B908EA89B733966B20D5CE0EFE7ABFF1" box="[420,510,1914,1937]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">A. quito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D18B733966B2353CE0EFC23BFF2" authority="Curletti &amp; Brule, 2011" authorityName="Curletti &amp; Brule" authorityYear="2011" box="[546,935,1913,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perditus">
<emphasis id="B908EA89B733966B2353CE0EFD1ABFF1" box="[546,670,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">A. perditus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B6AB733966B23D7CE0DFC23BFF2" author="Curletti" box="[678,935,1913,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" refString="Curletti, G. &amp; Brule, S. (2011) Agrilus, Agriloides et Autarcontes de Guyane. Magellanes ed. Ex Natura, 2, 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="2011">
Curletti &amp; Brûlé, 
<number id="3DB424BCB733966B2201CE0EFC23BFF2" box="[880,935,1914,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<typeStatus id="54C78839B733966B22C6CE0EFC6DBFF2" box="[951,1001,1914,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">type</typeStatus>
in MCCI- from French 
<collectingCountry id="F36B760BB733966B258FCE0EFADDBFF2" box="[1278,1369,1914,1938]" name="Guyana" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Guyana</collectingCountry>
. Both have the head with a red vertex, and a green pronotum, but they differ in the following main characters: 
<emphasis id="B908EA89B732966A21EEC9B8FC15B881" box="[159,913,204,225]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D18B732966A21EEC9B8FF6BB881" box="[159,239,204,225]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quito">A. quito</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D18B732966A2255C9B8FC15B881" box="[804,913,204,225]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perditus">A. perditus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369BB732966A21EEC982FCFDB91C" blockId="5.[159,1421,204,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">- Dorsal color more brilliant. - Dorsal color darker and less bright. - Sculpture of vertex with strong longitudinal stripes. - Sculpture of vertex punctiform. - Pronotum wider on posterior half, strongly sinuate before the - Pronotum wider on anterior half with posterior angles more basal angles that are more acute. squared.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369BB732966A21EEC8E5FBBCB9C6" blockId="5.[159,1421,204,463]" box="[159,1080,400,422]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">- Elytral pubescence yellow. - Elytral pubescence white.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369BB732966A21EEC8CEFBDAB9AF" blockId="5.[159,1421,204,463]" box="[159,1118,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">
- Metatarsal formula 
<number id="3DB424BCB732966A2004C8CDFEFAB9AF" box="[373,382,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="1.0">1</number>
&lt;
<number id="3DB424BCB732966A20FEC8CDFE1AB9AF" box="[399,414,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DB424BCB732966A20DFC8CDFE3FB9AF" box="[430,443,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="3.0">3</number>
. - Metatarsal formula 
<number id="3DB424BCB732966A2288C8CDFB86B9AF" box="[1017,1026,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="1.0">1</number>
= 
<number id="3DB424BCB732966A2563C8CDFBA4B9AF" box="[1042,1056,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DB424BCB732966A2541C8CDFBB8B9AF" box="[1072,1084,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="3.0">3</number>
+ 
<number id="3DB424BCB732966A253DC8CDFBDEB9AF" box="[1100,1114,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="4.0">4</number>
.
</paragraph>
